The paper focuses on improving user control in text-retrieval systems, specifically through the use of visualizations. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of color term highlighting also suggests a potential focus on natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the study of user reactions to the visualization suggests a potential focus on user interface design (cs.UI). Finally, the use of a document viewer and the study of objective results suggests a potential focus on machine learning and deep learning (cs.DL).
